topics.body:
Speaking of trolls I have a feeling 2000-2020 in history books is probably going to be labeled "the decades humans didn't know how to use the internet properly" or such.

What I mean by this is look at the internet; 90% of the people who unironically shit talk about behind 7 proxies or screamers or such are people who just had their testicles drop and/or are just using the internet for the first time.

An example of this is if you ever play say call of duty or such most of the time someone shit talks our threatens to "haxors" you or calls you a "hacker" if you are too good have voices so high pitched that the only way to emulate it for men is to get kicked in the groins.

Why are there so many squeekers or such on the internet?  Easy cause a decade ago there was only 1 billion internet users, now there's over 2 billion and a decade from now there's going to be about 6 billion.  If you have that many people joining the internet for the first time there's going to be a lot of squeekers.

topics.body:
I was bored

"What do you mean 'we'?" a gaunt girl complained. She wiped the dust off of her raggedy dress, then continued, "You know I hate corpses, even if I haven't eaten in days, I still won't eat one" she scoffed and ran her fingers through her brown hair.

"You're not even real. I am just talking at a mirror for Christ's sake!"

"I am real though!" th reflection said taken aback. It whimpered.

"Oh, piss off!"

"Look, just eat the fucking corpse and I'll stop 'mildly' annoying you".

The girl shook her head then took a brick from a pile of rubble behind her.

"I'm done, I am so fucking done with you annoying me! I came here looking for real food!" she held the brick tightly in her grasp, "and I mean normal people food, you, you useless piece of shit!".

She was about to throw the brick with all the strength she could muster. All of a sudden a thumping noise followed by the sound of shattering echoed throughout the room.

"Hah! I win, bitch!", the reflection cheered. A shotgun shell ejected as she pumped the gun. Brain matter, blood, and bits of skull were scattered across the room and the brick laid in pieces adjacent to her.

"
